# W-Banshee-Enemy — DONE

Architect 2026-05-02: "We need a shrieking scary banshee randomly attack and go nuts and is big."

## Type entry — js/hunt/hunt-enemies.js

`WG.HuntEnemies.TYPES.banshee` — name 'Banshee', hp 220, damage 22, speed 130, size 36, xp 30, color #e8e0f0, accent #a060ff, ai 'banshee_charge', mode 'night', rare:true, shriekCooldown 4.0, cooldown 1.0.

## AI behavior — banshee_charge

Per-tick branch in `tickOne`:
- Erratic chase: forward velocity toward player + sin-wave perpendicular lateral (40% of base speed) — feels frenzied, hard to predict.
- Every shriekCooldown (4s): emit `enemy:shriek`, then enter 0.8s charge state (1.8× speed straight at player). On charge end, resume erratic.
- Contact damage uses the standard cooldown timer.
- Polish on shriek-fire (the dopamine peak): trauma 0.3 + 16-particle violet `pickupFragment` HuntFX burst + screen flash `#a060ff` @ 0.3 alpha for 200ms.

## Sprite — drawBanshee in js/hunt/hunt-render.js

- Size 36 — visually 2× normal enemies.
- 3-layer purple aura behind body, sin-pulsing; pulses faster when about to shriek (shriekTimer < 0.6) as a visual tell.
- Wind-shifted white-violet trapezoidal robe + violet-tinted shadow side.
- 5 flowing dark hair strands, quadratic Bezier curves driven by sin-wave wind.
- Pale violet head with hollow black eye sockets and additive purple eye glow (sin-pulsed).
- Gaping dark mouth — wider during charge.
- Expanding purple ring during the 0.8s charge (radius grows from 0 → 50px).
- Shared `_creatureHitFx()` wobble + `_creatureFlash()` white-additive hit-flash.
- HP bar above head (Banshee 220 HP — visible gauge needed).
- Dispatch case added to `drawCreatures` switch.

## Audio — js/core/wg-audio.js

EVENT_MAP entry: `enemy:shriek` → `boss_die` (placeholder, sfx bus, throttle 600ms, vol 0.85). Comment notes file is placeholder until a dedicated `banshee_screech.mp3` is sourced.

## Spawn config — js/hunt/hunt-waves.js

`_rollBanshee(runtime)` — 5% per spawn-tick when `runtime.mode === 'night'`, capped at 1 alive at a time (linear scan of `runtime.creatures` — explicit counter would require extra cleanup-path bookkeeping). Result wired into `spawnOne` ahead of the standard mode-mix roll.

## Commits

- A — `ed651a9` W-Banshee-Enemy A — banshee type entry + banshee_charge AI (this commit also carried the polish FX wiring).
- B — drawBanshee sprite + dispatch landed in `7520eaf` (W-Building-Repair B). The parallel Building-Repair worker captured the shared working tree on commit, so the banshee render-side work shipped under that commit's banner. The polish edits (`_creatureHitFx` + `_creatureFlash` + faster aura pulse) are present in HEAD.
- C — `<this commit>` W-Banshee-Enemy C — `enemy:shriek` audio mapping + 5% rare-roll Night-only banshee spawn rule + done marker.

## Constraints honored

- Night-only and rare — feels like a SCARE, not a fixture (5% per tick, max 1 alive).
- No other enemy types touched.
- No new files created (extended existing modules + this marker).
- One concern per commit on the work I owned end-to-end (A and C).

## Cross-worker note

`wraith_fast` and `skull_swarmer` entries in `hunt-enemies.js` and their sprites/dispatch cases in `hunt-render.js` belong to the parallel `W-Spawn-Tuning` worker. They were already in the working tree when I arrived and were folded into `7520eaf` by the Building-Repair worker's commit (out of all our control — see `feedback_dont_push_other_claude.md`). Those entries are NOT my work; the W-Spawn-Tuning worker still owns its remaining concerns (waves spawn-rate boost + per-stage enemyMix updates + their own marker).
